events.event_name: Philippines December 2025 Labor Force Survey Release
events.description: The release of labor market data for December 2025, including unemployment and employment figures.

facts.fact_text: The unemployment rate in the Philippines was 4.4% in December 2025.

evidences.evidence_text: The unemployment rate in the Philippines remained at 4.4% in December 2025, unchanged from November

facts.fact_text: The unemployment rate in December 2024 was 3.1%.

evidences.evidence_text: it was higher than the 3.1% recorded in December 2024

facts.fact_text: The number of unemployed persons in the Philippines reached 2.26 million in December 2025.

evidences.evidence_text: The number of unemployed persons rose slightly to 2.26 million from 2.25 million in November

facts.fact_text: The services sector accounted for 62.4% of total employment.

evidences.evidence_text: services continued to dominate employment at 62.4% of total workers

facts.fact_text: The labor force participation rate was 64.4% in December 2025.

evidences.evidence_text: The labor force participation rate was 64.4%, up from 64.0% in November

claims.claim_text: The labor market conditions in the Philippines are stable.
